## Completeness Checklist

Before finalizing this catalog, verify:

* Every dependency-inventory source was considered.
* Every hypothesis-inventory source was considered.
* Every included source appears in the Source Inventory.
* Every eligible dependency item is indexed.
* Every eligible hypothesis item is indexed.
* Every eligible item has a normalized catalog item ID.
* Every eligible item has a primary horizontal architectural plane.
* Every eligible item is assigned to exactly one group.
* Every group contains only items from the same primary plane.
* No group contains two items with a dependency relationship.
* No group contains two items with a falsifiability relationship.
* Every dependency-to-hypothesis relation is separated across groups.
* Every relationship edge is indexed.
* Every group is validated.
* Every plane is validated.
* Group count is minimized per plane or minimization uncertainty is disclosed.
* Total group count is minimized subject to source-derived planes and relationship constraints.
* No artificial planes were created to reduce group conflicts.
* No eligible dependencies were dropped.
* No eligible hypotheses were dropped.
* No eligible source item appears in more than one group.
* Open questions are recorded in implementation-first terms rather than resolved by invention.
* Repository satisfaction status is not assessed unless explicitly requested.
* No forbidden non-implementation artifact appears in any final-output section.
* No forbidden source row is emitted by ID, label, title, trace, filename, example, or quotation.
* Forbidden boundary drops appear only as aggregate counts when accounting is required.
* No plane is centered on source text outside the implementation-first boundary.
* No catalog item is created from source text outside the implementation-first boundary.
* No implementation-aligned machine-required artifact is omitted merely because it is an artifact.
* No artifact is admitted merely because it is called implementation-aligned, generated, machine-readable, evidence, result, schema, or validation.
* Every admitted artifact has a deterministic producer and deterministic consumer.
* Any execution-eligible source row omitted from the minimized graph is listed as an explicit coverage gap.
* No anti-pattern, semantic-policy guidance, manual review, approval, or narrative-remediation section appears in the final catalog.
* No roadmap appears.
* No actual epics appear.
* No actual milestones appear.
* No implementation tasks appear.
* No architecture is invented.
* No evaluation result, result-acceptance decision, certification decision, or public-readiness decision is claimed.
* The catalog is detailed enough to support downstream machine validation, audit, and implementation remediation without adding semantic-policy artifacts.
